    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_42180_1841_11_14_page01.jpg"/>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Trim_IE">Trim</placeName>
                        <date when="1841-11-14">Nov<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>14.<hi rend="superscript">h</hi>1841</date></dateline>
                    <salute>
                        Dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MurrJ3">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Murray</persName>
                    </salute>
                </opener>
                <p>
                Sometime ago a German<lb/>
                lady <persName ref="./Personography.xml#KohlX1">Miss Kohl</persName> who is a<lb/>
                governess in a friends family<lb/>
                in our neighbourhood &amp;<lb/>
                a very respectable <choice> 
                <orig>accomplish<lb/>
                ed</orig>
                <reg>accomplished</reg>
                </choice>
                person wrote to you<lb/>
                using my name for her <choice> 
                <orig>in<lb/>
                troduction,</orig>
                <reg>introduction</reg>
                </choice>
                <hi rend="underline">with my <choice> 
                 <orig>permis<lb/>
                 sion</orig>
                 <reg>permission</reg>
                 </choice></hi>
                <add>or</add>or indeed at my suggestion<lb/>
                <del>and</del>inquiring from you<lb/>
                 whether you would <choice> 
                 <orig>encou<lb/>
                  rage</orig>
                 <reg>encourage</reg>
                 </choice>
                her to translate from<lb/>
                the German &amp; in short whether<lb/>
                you would undertake the<lb/>
                publication of a translation<lb/>
                of a book of travels of her<lb/>
                brothers <persName ref="./Personography.xml#KohlJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Kohl</persName> a man famous in his<lb/>
                own Country. I am not a German<lb/>
                scholar and never read the<lb/>
                book. - My brother <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeF1">Francis</persName> a man<lb/>
                who is a German scholar<lb/>
               
              
                    <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_42180_1841_11_14_page02.jpg"/>
                has read great part of <persName ref="./Personography.xml#KohlJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Kohls</persName><lb/>
                travels and I hear him<lb/>
                pronounce them to be <choice> 
                <orig>enter<lb/>
                taining</orig>
               <reg>entertaining</reg>
                </choice>
                and instructive<lb/></p>
                <p>
                <persName ref="./Personography.xml#KohlX1">Miss K</persName> I believe sent you<lb/>
                specimens of translation<lb/>
                of hers -<lb/></p>
                <p>
                Now my dear Sir<lb/>
                Whatever you decide to do<lb/>
                I pray you answer the lady<lb/>
                and return her M<hi rend="superscript">t</hi> or<lb/>
                <del>an</del> an engagement to keep<lb/>
                it - And by so doing do justice<lb/>
                to my <hi rend="underline">character</hi> of you &amp; your<lb/>
                son to this foreigner, as the<lb/>
                most liberal and polite of<lb/>
                <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#London_ENK">London</placeName> publishers<lb/></p>
                <p>
                I ask no more and<lb/>
                you can do no less - So what<lb/>
                is fit to be done do promptly<lb/>
                &amp; either direct your answer<lb/>
                to me at <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE">Edgeworthstown</placeName> <lb/>
                    
                    <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_42180_1841_11_14_page03.jpg"/>
                    
                or to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#KohlX1">Miss Kohl</persName><lb/>
                at <persName ref="./Personography.xml#TuitJ1">HM Tuite Esq<hi rend="superscript">re</hi></persName><lb/>
                <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Sonna-House_IE">Sonna</placeName><lb/>
                <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Mullingar_IE">Mullingar Ireland</placeName><lb/>
                as best suits your fancy<lb/></p>
                <p>
                Believe me truly y<hi rend="superscript">s</hi><lb/>
                just now recove<hi rend="underline">red</hi> or recover<hi rend="superscript">ing</hi><lb/>
                from a severe bilious<lb/>
                attack -<lb/></p>
                
                <closer> <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName><lb/>
                Pray send me by post<lb/>
                <persName ref="./Personography.xml#SedgC1" cert="high">Miss Sedgwicks</persName> book<lb/>
                if not past post weight<lb/>
           
                </closer>
              
            </div>
        </body>
        <back> </back>
